# ============================================================================
# CORS CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
# Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) settings
# Controls which domains can make requests to your API
#
# DEVELOPMENT: All origins allowed by default (CORS_ALLOW_ALL_ORIGINS=True)
# PRODUCTION: Must explicitly list allowed origins (comma-separated)
#
# Requirements for production:
# - All origins MUST use HTTPS (http:// not allowed)
# - Include your frontend domain(s)
# - Include any mobile app domains
# - Do NOT use wildcards in production
#
# Examples:
# Single origin: CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://app.tulia.ai
# Multiple origins: CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://app.tulia.ai,https://admin.tulia.ai,https://mobile.tulia.ai
#
# For local development with frontend:
# CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:3001
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY HEADERS
# ============================================================================
# Additional security headers are automatically configured:
# - SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT: Redirects HTTP to HTTPS (production only)
# - SECURE_HSTS_SECONDS: HTTP Strict Transport Security (1 year in production)
# - SECURE_CONTENT_TYPE_NOSNIFF: Prevents MIME type sniffing
# - SECURE_BROWSER_XSS_FILTER: Enables XSS filter
# - X_FRAME_OPTIONS: Prevents clickjacking (DENY)
# - SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE: Secure cookies (production only)
# - CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE: Secure CSRF cookies (production only)
#
# These are configured automatically based on DEBUG setting.
# No additional configuration needed.
